# Rust
/target/
**/target/
Cargo.lock.bak
*.pdb

# Node — the TypeScript toolchain's resolved installs (ts-extract dev
# deps, the ts-demo's devDependencies). Lockfiles ARE committed; the
# shippable-tree filter excludes node_modules from package hashes too
# (PROP-024 §2.2).
**/node_modules/

# vibevm internal cache (per-project, gitignored per spec §4.2)
.vibe/

# Editor / OS
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# Claude Code per-developer local settings — machine-scoped, not shared.
.claude/settings.local.json

# Agent skill projections — written by `vibe skill install` from the
# installed packages' [[skill]] declarations; reproducible, per-developer.
.claude/skills/
.opencode/
.agents/

# Reference sources and author's book chapters — cloned/placed externally,
# not part of the vibevm distribution. Kept out of git both to respect
# upstream copyright and to keep the public repo lean.
/refs/

# ProjectX design captures (reference screenshots under refs/screens/projectx/).
# The owner requires these NEVER enter git. Redundant with /refs/ above and kept
# deliberately explicit — belt-and-suspenders, so the guarantee survives any future
# change to the /refs/ rule. Both an anchored and a recursive form for certainty.
/refs/screens/projectx/
**/refs/screens/projectx/

# Local playgrounds for hand-testing M0 (not source of truth)
/playground/

# The local intent ledger (LEDGER-INTENT v0.1) — derived interpretations cache, never shipped.
/.ledger/
